data.title: Eleanor of Alburquerque
data.meta_description: Eleanor of Alburquerque was a Castilian noblewoman, Countess of Alburquerque, who became Queen of Aragon by her marriage to Ferdinand I of Aragon. She was the regent of Aragon during the absence of her son the king in 1420.
